# cuda busy loop kernel
Run busy loop kernel with 48K of shared memory on NVIDIA T1000

## Build

    make

## Run

### Options

    -d, GPU device ID, default = 0
    -n, GPU kernel block number, default = 14
    -s, GPU kernel block size, default = 1024
    -t, Loop time in second, default = 1, set 0 for endless
    -h, Disaply usage

### Default mode

    ./busy_loop

    Device ID = 0
    Block number = 14
    Block size = 1024
    Loop time = 1

### Endless mode

    ./busy_loop -t 0

    Device ID = 0
    Block number = 14
    Block size = 1024
